WOW, what a weekend.&nbsp; Friday night was Adult Championships, somehow during the last game a fight broke out due to a couple smart mouths so the Championships ended on a bit of a sour note.&nbsp; We didn't arrive home until nearly midnight and it took all of us about an hour to wind down before we could go to bed.

Bright and early at 5am on Saturday morning, we all got a wake-up call to get ready to leave for the Children's Championships. Ugh!&nbsp; Four hours sleep!&nbsp; So we wake up, fight over the shower for a bit, load up the van, and head out by 5:50am.&nbsp; We arrive at the park at 5:55am.&nbsp; From that point until 7pm, we are outside working the Championships.&nbsp; I was helping to run the snack tent, selling coffee, candy, chips, soda, water and hot dogs.

The first game of the day was the Squirt girls, Jessica's team (sitting in last place with only one win the entire season) against the second place team.&nbsp; Holy cow!&nbsp; What an amazing game!&nbsp; Jessie's team had a lot of heart and they played like they had never played before.&nbsp; The game runs for 7 innings but at the end of the second inning, they were tied and went into extra innings.&nbsp; Three additional innings later, Jessica's team WON!&nbsp; That's right!&nbsp; They won!&nbsp; That game had everyone in the park, even those who were there and not part of the games were sitting on the edge of their seats.&nbsp; The girls drew a huge crowd.&nbsp; 

There was a 10 minute break and then Jessica's team had to play against the first place team.&nbsp; The crowd continued to grow and ALL the stands were filled and all the spaces in between were filled with people sitting on the grass watching the game.&nbsp; What another great game!&nbsp; While it didn't go into extra innings, woah the girls really pulled it out.&nbsp; Jessica's team was getting stomped in the beginning but out of nowhere they pulled it together and managed to tie it up.&nbsp; We thought they would be going into extra innings but in the last inning, Jessie's team grabbed 4 extra runs and it was all over.&nbsp; 

A team that came into the Championships with only one win the entire season came away the Champions.&nbsp; It just goes to show that you should never give up and count yourself out because if you try your hardest, you can accomplish anything.

Unfortunately, because Jessica's games were first AND ran into so many extra innings, it caused all the other games for the rest of the day to be delayed so&nbsp; instead of ending at 4pm, we were there until 7pm. 

All in all, everyone had fun.&nbsp; We had two diamonds going, the main one for fast pitch and the small one for the t-ball players.&nbsp; During Championships, the diamonds get chalked, which the kids love.&nbsp; For the fast pitch, there are two umpires and for t-ball there is just one.&nbsp; In addition, for the Championships, the games are announced on a PA system so the kids really have fun with it.&nbsp; They created nicknames for themselves such as Trevor the Terminator.&nbsp; The announcers really made it fun for the kids, they were laughing, taking bows and so on.&nbsp; 

By the time the games ended, we had packed up and left (7pm) we were all exhausted and sunburned.&nbsp; Unfortunately, our day was not over.&nbsp; We had just enough time to go home, unpack, change and leave because it was Ryan's birthday and we were meeting the grandparents and aunt at the restaurant of Ryan's choosing for his birthday dinner.&nbsp; We could barely move but we made it to the restaurant, then back to the house to open presents and eat cake.&nbsp; Within 5 minutes of the grandparents and aunt leaving, the entire house was in bed and asleep as fast as our heads hit the pillows.&nbsp; WHEW!

While I would love to say that Sunday, we all got to stay home and relax but, alas, that isn't the case.&nbsp; All the women in the house had a baby shower to attend.&nbsp; We were still very exhausted from the night before, but we dragged ourselves to the baby shower of a family friend.

I'm only now just starting to feel like I am recovering from the event.&nbsp; LOL.&nbsp; Even my face is starting to recover as is evident from my nose which is now peeling.

Tonight was a total family night.&nbsp; It started at dinner time.&nbsp; We all (except Ryan and his father who were working) headed to Kelsie's for dinner.&nbsp; On the way home we picked up two movies... Spy Kids 3-D (for Jessie) and Cold Creek Manor (for my mother-in-law).&nbsp; We watched Spy Kids first.&nbsp; 

3-D movies suck.&nbsp; Let me just say that one more time.&nbsp; 3-D movies suck.&nbsp; Halfway through the movie, I got a splitting headache from the 3-D glasses.&nbsp; By the time the movie was done, my vision was totally messed up, my head hurt bad and to make things worse, the movie sucked.&nbsp; LOL.

Shortly after Spy Kids ended, Ryan and Charlie came home from work.&nbsp; We watched an episode of Outer Limits before starting the next movie, Cold Creek Manor.&nbsp; Ok, admittedly, the movie sucked.&nbsp; Ryan and Charlie, however, insisted on razzing Helen (my mother-in-law) repeatedly for choosing the movie.&nbsp; 

So here's a little about Cold Creek Manor.&nbsp; It stars Dennis Quaid and Sharon Stone.&nbsp; Trying to escape the dangers of living in New York City, the couple and their two kids buy a farmhouse manor in a small town.&nbsp; They got a great deal on the dilapidated home and all its contents inside.&nbsp; They discover that their dream home is more of a nightmare when the previous owner (Stephen Dorff) has recently been let out of prison and comes home only to find that it had been sold by the bank (they repossessed the home).&nbsp; The previous owner decides he wants the house back along with all its secrets.

Ok, at first glance, it sounds like it could be a good movie and the trailers certainly make it out to be a scary movie.&nbsp; Unfortunately, the story has no depth.&nbsp; For example, there is a scene where the wife (Stone) is propositioned by her boss.&nbsp; He basically says, have an affair with me and I'll make you Vice President of the company.&nbsp; The scene fades, the son nearly gets hit by a car and then they move to the small town.&nbsp; The near affair is only mentioned one other time.&nbsp; So what was the point of even putting it into the movie?&nbsp; Where was the rest of it?&nbsp; Either finish the thought or don't put it in the movie at all.

The town slut (Juliette Lewis), what was her role other than the girlfriend of the ex-con previous owner?&nbsp; Her sister was the town sheriff but she really didn't do much in the movie.&nbsp; The ex-con's father, what role did he really play?&nbsp; None that I could see.&nbsp; In fact, the only character who had any type of depth in the movie was the murdering ex-con/previous owner and even that was pretty minimal.&nbsp; I mean seriously.&nbsp; The dude gets out of jail, shows up at the house (inside the house rifling through a bunch of stuff), invites himself to dinner then lights up a joint as soon as he finishes eating and says "Can I ask a favor?&nbsp; I just got out of jail, I used to own this house and I need a job.&nbsp; Can I help you renovate the house?"&nbsp; I mean seriously!&nbsp; Would YOU let that person work on the property?&nbsp; The entire movie wasn't realistic, very cliche and plain boring.

Honestly, with a cast of Dennis Quaid, Sharon Stone and Juliette Lewis, I would have expected more.&nbsp; They are movie veterans.&nbsp; Couldn't they tell a bad script when they read it?&nbsp; All I can say is avoid watching this movie.&nbsp; Save the rental fees and get something worth watching.

In fact, the other day, Ryan and I rented some movies.&nbsp; Under the Tuscan Sun was pretty good.&nbsp; Ryan and I both enjoyed it.&nbsp; Ryan talked bad about the movie for months but he finally let me rent it and he ended up liking it.&nbsp; Hehe.&nbsp; Something's Got To Give was a great movie and I'm not really a fan of Jack Nickelson or Diane Keaton.&nbsp; We also saw School of Rock but I don't recommend it.&nbsp; It stars Jack Black (I believe), whom I'm not a fan of but Ryan wanted to see the movie.&nbsp; At the end of the movie, (the same night we watched Under the Tuscan Sun), Ryan said that Under the Tuscan Sun was far better.&nbsp; 

On Monday, we are going to rent some more movies because Ryan has the day off.&nbsp; I know it's rare right now but he actually has a day off so we are going to relax and watch some movies and spend the day together.&nbsp; Anyway, we plan to rent The Matrix Revolutions and something else but we haven't decided on that yet.&nbsp; I haven't heard too many good reviews about it but after seeing the first two, I have to see how it ends.&nbsp; 

That's all for tonight everyone, have a good weekend and don't forget to move your clocks an hour ahead for Daylight Savings.

I know; I know, I have posted a lot today.&nbsp; Quite a change from the normal but apparently I've had a lot to say today.&nbsp; 

This most recent installment is about the great love in my life... my husband.&nbsp; I simply have the best and most amazing husband in the universe.&nbsp; Let me just give you a couple examples of how amazing he is. 

Last night, my husband, Ryan, was playing an online game called Planetside.&nbsp; Ryan is the Project Manager/Senior Editor of <a href="http://planetside.stratics.com/">Planetside Stratics</a>.&nbsp; To be a good PM, he needs to know and understand the game, so he plays when he has the time.&nbsp; Last night, he was playing and in the middle of an intense battle, with bullets rushing at him from all angles, I got up and gave him a kiss on the cheek.&nbsp; I didn't want to disturb him but wanted to show him a little love to let him know I was thinking of him.&nbsp; You won't believe what he did next... he stopped, turned toward me and gave me a long, passionate kiss.&nbsp; Yep, that's right.&nbsp; My husband stopped what he was doing and gave me enormous amounts of love, right there and then.&nbsp; He could have kept on playing, it wouldn't have bothered me.&nbsp; He didn't even have to acknowledge the kiss that I gave him but he did.&nbsp; He stopped it all and gave me all his attention.&nbsp; To anyone who is not a gamer or doesn't know a gamer wouldn't understand the importance of this gesture but for those who do, they understand.

Later on, we finally went to bed.&nbsp; It was 5am, we were both dead tired.&nbsp; In fact, he played until that time and I crashed out on the couch near him.&nbsp; We have this little rule that we don't go upstairs to bed without the other, so if one person wants to sleep, they sleep on the couch until the other is ready to go to bed.&nbsp; It's our way of always being near one another.&nbsp; Anyway, so here we are in bed ready to pass out, I'm getting settled in, snuggling up to Ryan and all of a sudden he steals some of the covers.&nbsp; We call that pre-stealing.&nbsp; You see, every night I fight my husband for the covers because he is always stealing them while we sleep.&nbsp; So he pre-stole about 4 inches or so of covers.&nbsp; Woah!&nbsp; Them's fighting words!&nbsp; HAHA.&nbsp; So I did what any normal, freezing wife would do.... I stole ALL the covers.&nbsp; Yes, all of them; top sheet and both comforters.&nbsp; So we playfully wrestled with the covers for about 30 minutes, then I decided to take not only all the covers but all the pillows too.&nbsp; (We have two pillows each)&nbsp; HAHA.&nbsp; His face was classic.&nbsp; He was in shock because I'd never done that before.&nbsp; Then somehow I managed to slowly push him OFF the bed.&nbsp; HAHA.&nbsp; He retaliated by stealing my side of the bed but finally begged me to let him have his side back because it has the appropriate "dip".&nbsp; HAHA.&nbsp; Eventually, I gave in and remade the bed&nbsp; (since the covers were all bunched up) and then we settled down but we had a grand time for about an hour.&nbsp; 

Ryan and I have such a great time together, filled with lots of love, respect and fun.&nbsp; Ryan appreciates everything that I do, whether it is making the bed each day, doing the laundry, washing dishes or whatever.&nbsp; He lets me know every time I do something how much he appreciates it.&nbsp; He doesn't care whether I am perfect or not, he overlooks any imperfections within me.&nbsp; All he cares about is whether I love him or not.&nbsp; Not only do I love him, but I love him with every ounce of energy pulsing within my body and show him every moment.&nbsp; We have the most amazing relationship and I'm thankful every day for having him in my life.

FAE+1BY+1D, Ryan!&nbsp; I love you!

So what is it?&nbsp; In one of the most remarkable astronomical discoveries, a round mass, approximately 800 to 1,100 miles in diameter was discovered beyond Pluto.&nbsp; Scientists are conflicted about how to classify this mass.&nbsp; Is it a small planet?&nbsp; a planetoid?&nbsp; or is it simply a large and spectacular comet?&nbsp; The mass has been tentatively named Sedna, after the goddess in Inuit mythology who created sea creatures.

What I find to be funny is that scientists are slightly closed minded.&nbsp; It was only in 1930 that Pluto was discovered in the outer edges of our solar system and apparently there are still some scientists who don't believe that Pluto is actually a planet.&nbsp; While I am no scientist, I had always assumed that the vast majority of scientists have agreed to classify it as a planet.&nbsp; However, why is it that so many scientists aren't willing to accept the concept that there very well could be more planets out there in our solar system and we just lack the technology to see them.&nbsp; 

The question comes into play of whether or not scientists believe that we are the only planetary solar system in the universe. Think about this... how big is the universe?&nbsp; We don't know the answer to that question but have you ever tried to picture the end of the universe?&nbsp; Is there some wall where the universe simply ends?&nbsp; If so then wouldn't there be something behind the wall?&nbsp; Or what if the universe was round, like planets?&nbsp; Wouldn't there have to be an outer atmosphere if it was round?&nbsp; Wouldn't there be something above and below it?&nbsp; No matter how you try to picture it, there isn't an answer because no matter the answer, there's always an argument that could refute it to simply say, there is something beyond.&nbsp; 

Using the idea that the universe is an endless area, wouldn't it be possible that there are trillions of objects such as, comets, asteroids, stars, suns, moons, and, yes, planets that we have yet to discover?&nbsp; Just because we cannot "see" that far with our limited technology doesn't mean they don't exist.&nbsp; Who are we to say what is or is not a planet?&nbsp; I've never heard of a comet or asteroid that was perfectly round in shape, similar to a planet.&nbsp; 

Some scientists theorize that Sedna is a young planet, a small planet in the early stages of its existence.&nbsp; Other scientists have similar theories but feel that this young planet was knocked off course tossing it into the outer edges and because it was pushed so far out, the growth of this possible young planet was thwarted and it simply stopped evolving.

In continuing to read the article, it states that they believe that this "mass" has a moon circling it.&nbsp; So Sedna has a moon but is not a planet?&nbsp; What I also find to be interesting in the article is that the "mass" appears to be very red, nearly as red as Mars, which has the scientists baffled.&nbsp; All outer planets grow lighter in color, often white due to severe icing caused by its distance from the sun.&nbsp; Why then, is Sedna red?

The Hubble telescope is on the task.&nbsp; Scientists hope to learn more in a few days about Sedna but doubt that they will really learn that much.&nbsp; It is felt that New Horizons will give the true answers.&nbsp; 

New Horizons is the first exploration of the third zone of the solar system, it is a space probe, of sorts, that will be launched in 2006 on a mission to Pluto.&nbsp; It's purpose is to learn more about Pluto, a planet in controversy, get a good picture of Pluto and learn what lies beyond our visual scope of the solar system.&nbsp; New Horizons is expected to reach its destination by the year 2015.&nbsp; While the purpose of the probe was originally to learn more about Pluto and make a determination, once and for all, about whether it is a planet or an interstellar common object, it's purpose was also to learn what lies beyond.&nbsp; 

Pluto has a moon, which would lead credancy to the theory that it is, in fact, a planet, just as Sedna is believed to have a moon in its orbit.&nbsp; The difficulty lies in the fact that there is no specific definition of what makes a planet.&nbsp; Without a true definition, it cannot be disproved, nor proved.&nbsp; New Horizons hopes to educate us and through its discoveries, we may find that Sedna is, indeed, a planet and who knows, maybe find additional planets, or we may end up losing a planet if it is discovered that Pluto is <i>not</i> a planet after all.&nbsp; Only time and technology will tell.&nbsp; It does provoke some hard thoughts.

